radition while taking care to render the original text as accurately as possible.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aVerse satire, LatinvTranslations into English. 4aLiterature. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAncient Studies.  aClassics.  aCultural Studies.  aLiterature.1 aBraund, Susanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraund, Susanna.1 aJuster, A. M.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package Complete Collectionz978311041345808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook-Package Literaturez978311041354008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311045954840uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978081220769940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780812207699423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780812207699/original  a978-3-11-041345-8  Penn Press eBook Package Complete Collection  a978-3-11-041354-0  Penn Press eBook-Package Literature  a978-3-11-045954-8  University of Pennsylvania Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK